## Success Criteria

A valid result requires:

1. Statistical significance  
2. Reproducibility  
3. Robustness under all control tests  

---

## Null Result Interpretation

> Supports standard quantum mechanics:  
> no measurable influence from prior history beyond the current state  

---

## Positive Result Interpretation

Possible implications:

- Residual path-history dependence  
- Non-Markovian behaviour  
- Incomplete state description  
- Experimental artifact (must be ruled out)  

---

